==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Conventual
<hw>Con*ven"tu*al</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>conventualis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>conventuel</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to a convent; monastic.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A <xex>conventual</xex>
garb.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Conventual church</b></col>, <cd>a church attached or
belonging to a convent or monastery.</cd>
<rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conventual</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Conventual
<hw>Con*ven"tu*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who lives in a convent; a
monk or nun; a recluse.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Converge</ent>⟦br⟧
